article_title: Woman charged with DWI after I-35 rollover crash
article_text:
Woman charged with DWI after I-35 rollover crash (KXAN Photo/ Julie Karam)

AUSTIN (KXAN) — Austin police have charged a woman with a DWI after her car flipped on I-35 around 2:20 a.m. Friday morning.

Emergency crews had to pull the woman out of the car after the crash pinned her inside. The car rolled-over in the northbound lanes of I-35 near Airport Boulevard.

Officers said the woman was taken to the hospital to treat her injuries before being charged. According to Austin police, she was released from the hospital around 3:15 a.m. and arrested for a DWI shortly after. She is estimated to be in her 30s.
